mon_collector.py
================

Description
-----------
Script to collect monitoring data from monitoding provider and put it in to Redis.

Installing requirements
-----------------------
$ pip3 install -r requirements.txt
Or install packages with modules listed in requirements.txt provided by your OS package manager.

Configuring
-----------
Create file .mr.developer.cfg:
[monitoring]
url =  https://mon.example.com
user = monuser
paswd = monpaswd
hosts_key = dotm::mon::hosts
services_key = dotm::mon::services

Running
-------
$ python3 mon_collector.py

Testing
-------
$ redis-cli hgetall dotm::mon::hosts
$ redis-cli hget dotm::mon::services uk-www2


mon_api.py
==========

Description
-----------
Protorype of monitoring API to expose data collected by mon_collector.py via HTTP as JSON object.

Running
-------
$ python3 mon_api.py

Testing
-------
$ curl -i http://localhost:8081/mon/get/uk-www2
$ curl -i http://localhost:8081/mon/get/uk-www2/status
$ curl -i http://localhost:8081/mon/get/uk-www2/service_status

